        output='# GPU Procurement Costs, AI Infrastructure Spending, and AI Free Cash Flow Proxy Disclosures\n\n## 1. GPU Procurement & Capital Expenditure Disclosures\n\n### GPU-Related Capital Expenditure Language\nThe company explicitly identifies GPU procurement as a core component of its AI capital expenditure strategy:\n\n> *"We have made and intend to continue to make substantial capital expenditures to support the growth of our AI products, including costs related to obtaining third-party GPUs, manufacturing our own GPUs, and constructing, leasing, maintaining, enhancing, and expanding our data centers."*\n\n### GPU Cost as Proportion of Compute Infrastructure (Industry Benchmark Cited)\nDrawing on SemiAnalysis data, the company discloses the cost structure of building compute infrastructure:\n\n| Component | % of Total Capital Cost |\n|---|---|\n| Data center construction (shell, MEP, grid interconnection) | ~30% |\n| **Processor and critical IT equipment procurement (GPUs)** | **~70%** |\n\n> *"For most AI companies without a build cost advantage, their total capital cost of building compute infrastructure derives approximately 30% from data center construction costs…and approximately 70% from the cost of procuring processors and critical IT equipment."*\n\n### GPU Depreciation Expense (Operating Cost Impact)\n\n| Period | GPU Depreciation Increase | Context |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Q1 2026** | **$908 million** increase in R&D | Part of total R&D increase of $1,471 million (+162.0% YoY) |\n| **FY 2025** | **$1,673 million** increase in R&D | Part of total R&D increase of $3,888 million (+330.8% YoY) |\n\nAdditional R&D drivers tied to GPU/compute infrastructure:\n- Q1 2026: Higher cloud computing and data center infrastructure expenses of **$301 million**\n- FY 2025: Higher infrastructure and cloud computing expenses of **$1,440 million**\n\n---\n\n## 2. AI Infrastructure Capital Expenditures by Segment\n\n### Capital Expenditures by Segment (in millions)\n\n| Segment | Q1 2026 (Unaudited) | Q1 2025 | FY 2025 | FY 2024 | FY 2023 |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Space | $1,052 | $759 | $3,832 | $2,032 | $1,497 |\n| Connectivity | $1,332 | $814 | $4,178 | $3,498 | $2,455 |\n| **AI** | **$7,723** | **$2,567** | **$12,727** | **$5,633** | **$463** |\n| **Total CapEx** | **$10,107** | **$4,140** | **$20,737** | **$11,163** | **$4,415** |\n\n### AI CapEx Growth Analysis\n\n| Period | AI CapEx | YoY Change | Primary Driver |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Q1 2026 | $7,723M | +$5,156M vs. Q1 2025 | "Rapid expansion of terrestrial data centers, including development, construction, and equipping of new facilities and supporting infrastructure" |\n| FY 2025 | $12,727M | +$7,094M vs. FY 2024 | Data center build-out and compute infrastructure |\n| FY 2024 | $5,633M | +$5,170M vs. FY 2023 | Initial AI infrastructure scale-up |\n| FY 2023 | $463M | — | Nascent AI investment |\n\n### AI CapEx as % of Total CapEx\n\n| Period | AI CapEx / Total CapEx |\n|---|---|\n| Q1 2026 | **76.4%** |\n| FY 2025 | **61.4%** |\n| FY 2024 | **50.5%** |\n| FY 2023 | **10.5%** |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Property, Plant & Equipment — AI Infrastructure Components\n\n### Note 5: Property, Plant, and Equipment, Net (in millions)\n\n| Asset Category | March 31, 2026 | December 31, 2025 | Delta |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Servers and networking equipment** | **$23,850** | **$22,694** | **+$1,156** |\n| Satellites | $12,893 | $11,949 | +$944 |\n| Machinery and equipment | $8,020 | $6,343 | +$1,677 |\n| **Data center infrastructure** | **$2,965** | **$2,960** | **+$5** |\n| Launch sites | $2,479 | $2,404 | +$75 |\n| Land, buildings and improvements | $2,018 | $1,876 | +$142 |\n| Flight vehicle hardware | $1,459 | $1,689 | -$230 |\n| Leasehold improvements | $842 | $784 | +$58 |\n| **Construction-in-progress** | **$14,045** | **$4,604** | **+$9,441** |\n| **Total PP&E (gross)** | **$68,571** | **$55,303** | **+$13,268** |\n| Less: Accumulated depreciation | ($14,692) | ($12,701) | ($1,991) |\n| **PP&E, net** | **$53,879** | **$42,602** | **+$11,277** |\n\n**Key observations:**\n- **Construction-in-progress** surged from $4,604M to $14,045M (+$9,441M / +205%) in Q1 2026 alone, described as "primarily comprised of ongoing construction and expansion of the facilities and equipment as well as **AI infrastructure that has not yet been placed in service**."\n- **Servers and networking equipment** (the GPU-bearing asset class) grew $1,156M in Q1 2026, reaching $23,850M.\n\n### Depreciation & Capitalized Interest\n\n| Metric | Q1 2026 | Q1 2025 | FY 2025 |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Depreciation expense | $2,329M | $1,237M | — |\n| Capitalized interest (to CIP) | $7M | $0 | $169M |\n\nCapitalized interest relates to "significant long-term construction projects, such as the **AI infrastructure data centers** and launch facilities."\n\n### Space Segment Impairment\n- Q1 2025: **$24 million** impairment for write-off of damaged flight vehicles in the Space segment\n- Q1 2026: **$0** (no PP&E impairment charges)\n\n---\n\n## 4. AI Segment Financial Profile & Free Cash Flow Proxy\n\n### Q1 2026 AI Segment Income Statement (in millions)\n\n| Line Item | Q1 2026 |\n|---|---|\n| **AI Revenue** | **$818** |\n| Cost of revenue | $456 |\n| Research and development | $2,379 |\n| Selling, general and administrative | $463 |\n| Restructuring charges | $(11) |\n| Total costs and expenses | $3,287 |\n| **AI Loss from operations** | **$(2,469)** |\n\n### Q1 2026 AI Segment Supplemental Information\n\n| Metric | Q1 2026 |\n|---|---|\n| Depreciation and amortization | $1,493M |\n| Share-based compensation | $378M |\n| **Capital expenditures** | **$7,723M** |\n\n### AI Free Cash Flow Proxy (Q1 2026)\n\n| Component | Amount (in millions) |\n|---|---|\n| AI Revenue | $818 |\n| Less: AI Operating loss | $(2,469) |\n| Add back: D&A | $1,493 |\n| Add back: Share-based compensation | $378 |\n| **= AI Operating Cash Flow Proxy (EBITDA-based)** | **$(598)** |\n| Less: AI Capital expenditures | $(7,723) |\n| **= AI Free Cash Flow Proxy** | **$(8,321)** |\n\n### AI Segment Operating Loss Trend\n\n| Period | AI Loss from Operations | YoY Change | Primary Drivers |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Q1 2026 | $(2,469)M | +$1,533M worse | "Higher cloud computing and GPU depreciation costs, data center infrastructure and employee expenses, partially offset by higher revenue" |\n| FY 2025 | $(6,355)M | +$4,794M worse | "Higher cloud computing costs, facilities-related costs and employee expenses" |\n| FY 2024 | $(1,561)M | $2,412M improvement | — |\n| FY 2023 | $(3,973)M | — | — |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Contractual Commitments for AI Infrastructure\n\n### Non-Cancelable Contractual Commitments (as of March 31, 2026)\n\n| Year | Amount (in millions) |\n|---|---|\n| 2026 | $2,720 |\n| **2027** | **$21,476** |\n| 2028 | $1,250 |\n| 2029 | $4 |\n| 2030 | $1 |\n| Thereafter | $0 |\n| **Total** | **$25,451** |\n\n> *"The Company\'s unconditional obligations are non-cancelable contractual commitments primarily relate to the Company\'s investments in **AI infrastructure and third-party cloud capacity arrangements** and other service arrangements."*\n\n### Recent Material AI Infrastructure Transactions (Post-March 31, 2026)\n\n| Date | Transaction | Amount | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Apr 24, 2026 | **Valor Transaction III** | **$6,587M** | 5-year equipment lease with related party for AI infrastructure hardware |\n| Apr 30, 2026 | **Turbine Acquisition** | **~$2,000M** | Purchase of mobile gas turbines to power data centers |\n| May 3, 2026 | **Anthropic Cloud Services Agreement** | Undisclosed monthly fee through May 2029 | Compute capacity access agreement |\n| Q1 2026 | **Additional turbine purchase agreements** | **$925M** | Turbines for AI infrastructure through 2029 |\n| Prior | **Compute agreement** | **$8.5B deferred services fee** | Plus option agreement (Cursor call option) |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Aggregate Cash Flow Context\n\n### Investing Activities (in millions)\n\n| Period | Net Cash Used in Investing | Purchases of PP&E |\n|---|---|---|\n| Q1 2026 | $(16,724) | — |\n| Q1 2025 | $(4,170) | — |\n| FY 2025 | $(19,575) | $(20,737) |\n| FY 2024 | $(10,796) | $(11,163) |\n| FY 2023 | $(4,867) | $(4,415) |\n\nThe Q1 2026 investing outflow of **$16.7 billion** (annualized run-rate of ~$67 billion) dramatically exceeds the FY 2025 total of $19.6 billion, reflecting the acceleration of AI infrastructure deployment.\n\n### Financing Activities Supporting AI Investment\n\n| Period | Net Cash from Financing | Key Driver |\n|---|---|---|\n| Q1 2026 | $7,125M | SpaceX Bridge Loan proceeds ($17,950M) + stock proceeds ($7,420M), offset by debt repayments ($14,703M) and stock repurchases ($3,838M) |\n| FY 2025 | $26,350M | AI segment debt/financing arrangements (+$16,055M YoY increase) |\n| FY 2024 | $11,830M | — |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Forward-Looking AI Capital Expenditure Risk Disclosures\n\nThe company explicitly warns about the multi-year investment horizon:\n\n> *"We plan to allocate substantial capital to build our AI compute infrastructure, and we expect a **multi-year investment horizon** before these deployments translate into sustained positive AI Segment Adjusted EBITDA. Our AI segment has incurred significant operating losses since inception, and we may not achieve profitability in this segment, or, if achieved, sustain it, and there can be no assurance that the returns on our AI investments will be adequate to justify the capital deployed."*\n\n> *"We have incurred significant capital expenditures and expect to **increase our capital expenditures substantially in the future** in connection with the design, development, and deployment of our satellite constellations, launch vehicles, ground stations, manufacturing facilities, and programs, including Terafab, **AI compute infrastructure, data centers**, and other supporting infrastructure."*\n\n### Accumulated Deficit Context\n- **Accumulated deficit as of March 31, 2026: $41,311 million**\n- Net loss Q1 2026: $(4,276) million\n- Net loss FY 2025: $(4,937) million\n- Net loss FY 2023: $(4,628) million\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Key Q1 2026 AI Infrastructure Metrics\n\n| Metric | Q1 2026 Value |\n|---|---|\n| AI segment revenue | $818M |\n| AI segment operating loss | $(2,469)M |\n| AI segment D&A | $1,493M |\n| AI segment capital expenditures | $7,723M |\n| AI FCF proxy (EBITDA − CapEx) | ~$(8,321)M |\n| Servers & networking equipment (gross PP&E) | $23,850M |\n| Construction-in-progress (gross) | $14,045M |\n| Total non-cancelable contractual commitments | $25,451M |\n| GPU depreciation expense increase (R&D, YoY) | $908M |\n| Post-quarter AI hardware lease (Valor III) | $6,587M |\n| Post-quarter turbine acquisitions | ~$2,925M combined |',
